---
title: Creamy Garlic Spinach Ricotta Ravioli with Roasted Bell Pepper
description: Tender pasta pillows are good in any form, but they’re *especially* good when packed with spinach and ricotta. Add tender strips of roasted bell pepper and a cheesy garlic cream sauce to the mix and you’ve got yourself a winning dinner. Luckily, this elegant pasta is as easy to make as it is delicious. All you need is 35 minutes for this dish to hit your table.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/645123337c1133149f0d913f-d086647d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/649ae9a1c8e13be2fa91ddea.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 17 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1040 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-garlic-spinach-ricotta-ravioli-649ae9a1c8e13be2fa91ddea
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @bell pepper{1}(halved); remove stem and seeds. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Drizzle bell pepper halves with @olive oil{2%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; arrange cut sides down on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Peel @garlic{1%clove}; place clove in the center of a small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with @cooking oil{2%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cinch into a packet and place on same sheet.

Roast on top rack until bell pepper is lightly charred and garlic is softened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once bell pepper and garlic have roasted about 15 minutes, gently add @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%oz} to pot of boiling water; reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain and set aside. Keep empty pot handy for Step 5.

Once bell pepper and garlic are done roasting, carefully transfer to a #cutting board{}. Thinly slice bell pepper and gently mash garlic with a #fork{} until smooth.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pot used for pasta over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp}; stir until smooth.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Stir in bell pepper and mashed garlic. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir ravioli into pot with sauce. If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide between bowls; season with pepper. Garnish with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan. Serve.